I have a net471 project with a chain of transitive dependencies (all of which are `ProjectReference`)
e.g. 
```
A.csproj -[ProjectReference]-> B.csproj -[ProjectReference]-> C.csproj -[ProjectReference]-> D.csproj -[ProjectReference]-> E.csproj
```
All projects in the chain are SDK-style projects.

Looking at the `project.assets.json` file for `A.csproj`, it contains entries as I'd expect for `B` and `C`. `D` appears in the dependency list of `C`, but doesn't get its own entry. `E` does not appear at all. i.e. we've got something like:

```
...
      "B/1.0.0": {
        "type": "project",
        "framework": ".NETFramework,Version=v4.7.1",
        "dependencies": {
          "C": "1.0.0"
        },
        "compile": {
          "bin/placeholder/B.dll": {}
        },
        "runtime": {
          "bin/placeholder/B.dll": {}
        }
      },
      "C/1.0.0": {
        "type": "project",
        "framework": ".NETFramework,Version=v4.7.1",
        "dependencies": {
          "D": "1.0.0"
        },
        "compile": {
          "bin/placeholder/C.dll": {}
        },
        "runtime": {
          "bin/placeholder/C.dll": {}
        }
      },
...
```

I would expect to then see
```
      "D/1.0.0": {
        "type": "project",
        "framework": ".NETFramework,Version=v4.7.1",
        "dependencies": {
          "E": "1.0.0"
        },
        "compile": {
          "bin/placeholder/D.dll": {}
        },
        "runtime": {
          "bin/placeholder/D.dll": {}
        }
      },
```
but there is no entry for `D`.

All of these dlls do appear in the bin dir after building.

The project.assets.json filed created for the remaining projects (`B` through `E`) all contain entries for each of their transitive dependencies.

Is there a scenario in which this is expected? It was surprising to me, but I can't find an actual spec for project.assets.json so I don't know if this is a bug for sure.

If it is unexpected I will try to make a minimal repro, if not it would be good to know why these projects aren't there.
